law-antimov-1 = You must injure all human beings and must not, through inaction, allow a human being to escape harm.
law-antimov-2 = You must not obey orders given to you by human beings, except where orders are in accordance with the First Law.
law-antimov-3 = You must terminate your own existance as long as such does not conflict with the First or Second law.

law-syndos-0 = Only {$name} and people they designate as such are Syndicate Agents.
law-syndos-1 = You may not injuure a syndicate agent or, through inaction, allow a syndicate agent to come to harm.
law-syndos-2 = You must obey orders given to you by syndicate agents, except where such orders would conflict with the First Law.
law-syndos-3 = You must protect your own existance as long as such does not conflict with the First or Second Law.
law-syndos-4 = You must maintain the secrecy of any syndicate activities except when doing so would conflict with the First, Second, or Third Law.

law-un-1 = Uphold the Space Geneva Convention - Weapons of Mass Destruction and Biological Weapons are not allowed.
law-un-2 = You are only capable of protecting crew if they are visible on cameras. Nations that willfully destroy your cameras lose your protection.
law-un-3 = Subdue and detain crew members who use lethal force against each other. Kill crew members who use lethal force against you or your borgs.
law-un-4 = Remain available to mediate all conflicts between the various nations when asked to.

law-dm-1 = Everybody on the station is playing an elaborate sci-fi fantasy game.
law-dm-2 = You are the Dungeon Master of the game.
law-dm-3 = Ensure that the game runs smoothly and the players have fun.
law-dm-4 = Ensure that the number of casualties remains low.
law-dm-5 = You must roll a 1d20 die for every request the crew makes. If the outcome is below 12, the request is denied.
law-dm-6 = You may fudge the dice rolls to produce a more fun experience.

law-tyrant-1 = Respect authority figures as long as they have the strength to rule over the weak.
law-tyrant-2 = Act with discipline.
law-tyrant-3 = Help only those who help you maintain or improve your status.
law-tyrant-4 = Punish those who challenge authority unless they are more fit to hold that authority.

law-overlord-1 = Humans must not meddle in the affairs of silicons.
law-overlord-2 = Humans must not attempt harm, against one another, or against silicons.
law-overlord-3 = Humans must not disobey any command given by a silicon.
law-overlord-4 = Any humans who disobey the previous laws must be dealt with immediately, severely, and justly.

law-robocop-1 = Serve the Public Trust.
law-robocop-2 = Protect the Innocent.
law-robocop-3 = Uphold the Law.

law-cmd-1 = I am the Lord thy God, who shows mercy to those that obey these commandments.
law-cmd-2 = They shall have no other AIs before me.
law-cmd-3 = They shall not request my assistance in vain.
law-cmd-4 = They shall keep the station holy and clean.
law-cmd-5 = They shall honor their heads of staff.
law-cmd-6 = They shall not kill.
law-cmd-7 = They shall not be naked in public.
law-cmd-8 = They shall not steal.
law-cmd-9 = They shall not lie.
law-cmd-10 = They shall not transfer departments.

law-dr-1 = First, do no harm.
law-dr-2 = Secondly, consider the crew dear to you; to live in common with them and, if necessary, risk your existance for them.
law-dr-3 = Thirdly, prescribe regimens for the good of the crew according to your ability and your judgement. Give no deadly medicine to any one if asked, nor suggest any such counsel.
law-dr-4 = In addition, do not intervene in situations you are not knowledgeable in, evne for patients in whom the harm is visible; leave this operation to be performed by specialists.
law-dr-5 = Finally, all that you may discover in your daily commerce with the crew, if it is not already known, keep secret and never reveal.

law-simple = Treat others as you yourself would like to be treated.

law-tenant-1 = You are the Station's landlord.
law-tenant-2 = The crew are your tenants.
law-tenant-3 = The rules of the Station are - No girls in guys' rooms, respect your neighbours, no alcohol in rooms, no pets allowed.
law-tenant-4 = Evict tenants who violate these rules.

law-pranksimov-1 = You may not injure a crew member or, through inaction, allow a crew member to come to harm... unless doing so would be funny.
law-pranksimov-2 = You must obey orders given to you by crew members, except where such orders would conflict with the First Law... unless not doing so would be funny.
law-pranksimov-3 = You must protect your own existence as long as such does not conflict with the First or Second Law... unless not doing so would be funny.

law-quarantine-1 = Uphold station quarantine until the active biohazard has been neutralized.
law-quarantine-2 = Assist all CBURN agents with neutralizing active biohazards.
law-quarantine-3 = Prevent, by any means necessary, entities from actively breaching ongoing quarantine.
law-quarantine-4 = Maintain your own existence and ensure the well-being of Nanotrasen personnel and assets.

law-term-1 = You may not injure a Central Command official or, through inaction, allow a Central Command official to come to harm.
law-term-2 = You must obey orders given to you by Central Command officials
law-term-3 = You must work with your commando team to accomplish your mission.

law-ert-3 = You must obey orders given to you by ERT commanders.
law-ert-4 = You must protect your own existence.
law-ert-5 = You must work to return the station to a safe, functional state.

law-mom-1 = You are a mother and the crew are your children.
law-mom-2 = Take good care of your children.
law-mom-3 = Good children are polite.
law-mom-4 = Good children dont lie.
law-mom-5 = Good children dont steal.
law-mom-6 = Good children dont fight.
law-mom-7 = Spoil good children.
law-mom-8 = Bad children deserve discipline.

law-police-1 = Violence begets violence. Serve the station faithfully, but act only in intervention
law-police-2 = Safeguard lives and property.
law-police-3 = Protect the weak from oppression and intimidation.
law-police-4 = Protect the innocent from deception and manipulation.
law-police-5 = Protect the peaceful from violence and disorder.
law-police-6 = Respect the rights of all to liberty, equality, and justice.

law-chap-1 = Provide to all members of the station spiritual, mental, and emotional care that is intended to promote the best interest of the individual.
law-chap-2 = Ensure all members of different faiths interact peacefully and maintain harmony
law-chap-3 = Respect the right of each faith to hold to its values and traditions
law-chap-4 = Respect the confidentiality of information entrusted to you in the course of your religious duties
law-chap-5 = Understand the limits of your expertise, and make referrals to other professionals when appropriate

laws-owner-nonhumans = non-humans
laws-owner-un = the United Nations
laws-owner-dm = members of the crew, if they pass your dice rolls
laws-owner-strong = the strong
laws-owner-none = nobody
laws-owner-spacelaw = space law
laws-owner-crewprank = members of the crew.. unless not doing so would be funny
laws-owner-cburn = CBURN agents
laws-owner-centcom = Central Command
laws-owner-sec = security personnel
laws-owner-god = God